   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The following describes the dataset variables:\n",
    "\n",
    "·      CRIM - per capita crime rate by town\n",
    "\n",
    "·      ZN - proportion of residential land zoned for lots over 25,000 sq.ft.\n",
    "\n",
    "·      INDUS - proportion of non-retail business acres per town.\n",
    "\n",
    "·      CHAS - Charles River dummy variable (1 if tract bounds river; 0 otherwise)\n",
    "\n",
    "·      NOX - nitric oxides concentration (parts per 10 million)\n",
    "\n",
    "·      RM - average number of rooms per dwelling\n",
    "\n",
    "·      AGE - proportion of owner-occupied units built prior to 1940\n",
    "\n",
    "·      DIS - weighted distances to five Boston employment centres\n",
    "\n",
    "·      RAD - index of accessibility to radial highways\n",
    "\n",
    "·      TAX - full-value property-tax rate per $10,000\n",
    "\n",
    "·      PTRATIO - pupil-teacher ratio by town\n",
    "\n",
    "·      LSTAT - % lower status of the population\n",
    "\n",
    "·      MEDV - Median value of owner-occupied homes in $1000's"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Is there a significant difference in median value of houses bounded by the Charles river or not? (T-test for independent samples)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Levene Test\n",
    "* H0: The population variances are equal\n",
    "* H1: The population variances are not equal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 61,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "LeveneResult(statistic=8.75190489604598, pvalue=0.003238119367639829)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 61,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "scipy.stats.levene(boston_df[boston_df['CHAS'] == 0]['MEDV'], boston_df[boston_df['CHAS'] == 1]['MEDV'], center='mean')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the above Levene Test gives a P-value of 0.0032, which is less than 0.05, we reject the null hypotheses that the variances are equal and assume unequal variances"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "T-Test for independent samples\n",
    "* $H_0:$: The median value of houses bounded by the Charles river __DOES NOT__ differ significantly\n",
    "* $H_1:$: The median value of houses bounded by the Charles river __DOES__ differ significantly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 62,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Ttest_indResult(statistic=-3.113291312794837, pvalue=0.003567170098137517)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 62,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "scipy.stats.ttest_ind(boston_df[boston_df['CHAS'] == 0]['MEDV'], boston_df[boston_df['CHAS'] == 1]['MEDV'], equal_var = False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the above T-Test gives a P-value of 0.0036 which is less than 0.05, we __reject the null__ as there is sufficient evidence that the median value of houses bounded by the Charles river differs significantly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Is there a difference in Median values of houses (MEDV) for each proportion of owner occupied units built prior to 1940 (AGE)? (ANOVA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Levene Test\n",
    "* $H_0:$ The population variances are equal\n",
    "* $H_1:$ The population variances are not equal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 71,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "LeveneResult(statistic=2.78062002937483, pvalue=0.06295337343259205)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 71,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "scipy.stats.levene(boston_df[boston_df['age_group'] == '70 years and older']['MEDV'],\n",
    "                   boston_df[boston_df['age_group'] == 'Between 35 and 70 years']['MEDV'], \n",
    "                   boston_df[boston_df['age_group'] == '35 years and younger']['MEDV'], \n",
    "                   center='mean')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the above Levene Test gives a P-value of 0.063, which is greater than 0.05, we __fail to reject__ the null hypotheses that the variances are equal and assume equal variances"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "One-way ANOVA\n",
    "* $H_0:$ The median value of houses for each proportion of owner occupied units built prior to 1940 __DOES NOT__ differ significantly\n",
    "* $H_1:$ The median value of houses for each proportion of owner occupied units built prior to 1940 __DOES__ differ significantly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 73,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "seventy_older = boston_df[boston_df['age_group'] == '70 years and older']['MEDV']\n",
    "thirtyfive_seventy = boston_df[boston_df['age_group'] == 'Between 35 and 70 years']['MEDV']\n",
    "thirtyfive_lower = boston_df[boston_df['age_group'] == '35 years and younger']['MEDV']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 75,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "F-Statistic: 36.40764999196599, P-Value: 1.7105011022702984e-15\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f_statistic, p_value = scipy.stats.f_oneway(seventy_older, thirtyfive_seventy, thirtyfive_lower)\n",
    "print(\"F-Statistic: {0}, P-Value: {1}\".format(f_statistic, p_value))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the above ANOVA gives a P-value of 1.711e-15 which is less than 0.05, we __reject the null__ as there is sufficient evidence that the median value of houses for each proportion of owner occupied units built prior to 1940 differs significantly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Can we conclude that there is no relationship between Nitric oxide concentrations and proportion of non-retail business acres per town? (Pearson Correlation)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Pearson Correlation Test\n",
    "* $H_0:$ There is no correlation between Nitric-oxide concentrations and proportion of non-retail business acres per town\n",
    "* $H_1:$ There is a correlation between Nitric-oxide concentrations and proportion of non-retail business acres per town"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 77,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "PearsonRResult(statistic=0.7636514469209157, pvalue=7.91336106123623e-98)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 77,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "scipy.stats.pearsonr(boston_df['NOX'], boston_df['INDUS'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The corellation coefficient of 0.764 indicates a strong positive corellation between the two variables.\n",
    "\n",
    "Since the Pearson Correlation Test gives a P-Value of 7.91e-98, which is less than 0.05, we __reject the null__ as there is strong evidence that there is a corellation between Nitric-oxide concentrations and proportion of non-retail business acres per town"
   ]
  },
  {

    "## X is the input variables (or independent variables)\n",
    "X = boston_df['DIS']\n",
    "## y is the target/dependent variable\n",
    "y = boston_df['MEDV']\n",
    "## add an intercept (beta_0) to our model\n",
    "X = sm.add_constant(X) \n",
    "\n",
    "model = sm.OLS(y, X).fit()\n",
    "predictions = model.predict(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print out the statistics\n",
    "model.summary()"
   ]
